104
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:10,160
Another visual hierarchy tool at
your disposal is using bold

105
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,200
or italic weights.

106
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:15,890
Using these different weights
can add emphasis and intrigue

107
00:05:15,890 --> 00:05:17,090
to your design.

108
00:05:17,090 --> 00:05:20,740
However, using too much bold
can muddy your hierarchy.

109
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:24,510
It's almost as if everything is
screaming at you at once.

110
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:26,910
Also, make sure your
bold or italics

111
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:29,550
compliment the natural value.

112
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:33,100
For instance, the eye naturally
expects the headline

113
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:37,600
to be bolder than the body copy,
so by using a thin font

114
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:41,530
for your headline and a bold
font for your body copy,

115
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:43,710
you're going to confuse
the user.

116
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:46,880
When using bold or italic
weights, stick to a less is

117
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:49,210
more approach that will really
enhance your hierarchy.

